<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL &amp; CLOSURE</font><br>
<tt>Thu May  1 19:59:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
O.K.  You are who you are.  Like I am who I am.  Warts and all.  We move on.  I like the info passed around here.  The stories are a re-affermation of my thoughts.<br><br>
A story about the travelling Wall.<br>
I worked in a factory for eight years and knew them all by their names.  We vacationed together, partied together at work and on the weekends.  Itr was as much a social environment as it was a place to earn a paycheck.  Eight years later, I'm dead square in the middle of recovery and the traveling Wall comes to town.  It was suggested that I make a visit for some closure.  I said&quot; Cool&quot;.  Little wall, little reaction.  WRONGO!!!  I my wife had not been with me, as I pulled into the park where it was set up,  I wouldn't have gotten out of the truck.  It shook me to my core!  God, if this &quot;little wall&quot; did this to me how could I possibly survive THE WALL in D.C.?  Well, I got through my first time with the Wall.  Two years later it came back and I volunteered to help.  As I sat there helping find names and panel I looked up and there were five of the guys that I had worked with for 8 years!  Never Knew!  Never suspected or asked!  Blew me away.  We talked for hours and still remember each other that night.<br>
I finally got to see the Wall and it was all that I feared and longed for.  The closure, the purge of guilt, the closeness of those near me.  As I walked into it and got to the bottom and then walked out; it was if all the crap was left at the bottom and the coming out left only one way to go. Up!<br>
This 5/27/97 will be thirty years for me.  Sounds so long.  I will be in D.C. for the Rolling Thunder run and to greet my brothers that have come from all across the country to pay their respects. I will rejoice and cry tears of gladness for those names on the Wall have made me the man that I am today.  I will raise a glass to their sacrifice and make sure that they do not ever fade from anyone's memory.
